  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, Rockruff is a Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon that can be effective in battle with the right moveset. Here\u2019s a well-rounded moveset for Rockruff, focusing on its strengths:\n\n### Rockruff Moveset\n\n**Ability:** Keen Eye / Vital Spirit  \n**Nature:** Jolly (to boost Speed) or Adamant (to boost Attack)  \n**Item:** Life Orb / Choice Band / Focus Sash\n\n#### Moves:\n1. **Stone Edge** or **Rock Slide**  \n   - **Stone Edge**: High power and very strong STAB move, but less accurate.  \n   - **Rock Slide**: Lower power but has a chance to flinch; more accurate and useful for double battles.\n\n2. **Crunch**  \n   - Great for hitting Ghost- and Psychic-type Pok\u00e9mon, which can be a threat to Rockruff.\n\n3. **Close Combat**  \n   - Provides coverage against Steel, Rock, and Ice-types. Useful for hitting harder opponents.\n\n4. **Sucker Punch**  \n   - Great priority move to finish off weakened opponents or hit them before they can attack, especially when they are faster.\n\n### Alternative Options:\n- **Earthquake**: For coverage against Electric and Steel-types. This can be particularly useful if you anticipate facing a Pok\u00e9mon that might resist Rock-type moves.\n- **Howl**: Increases Attack and can be used to set up for a sweep, especially with Life Orb.\n  \n### Strategy:\n- Rockruff should be used as a fast physical attacker, capitalizing on its decent Speed and Attack stats. Priority moves like Sucker Punch can help it take down weakened foes.\n- Life Orb enhances damage output but also reduces HP, while Choice Band locks Rockruff into one move but significantly boosts its Attack. Focus Sash can allow it to survive a hit, enabling it to retaliate.\n\nBy leveraging its speed and access to powerful moves, Rockruff can be a dynamic threat on your team. Consider its synergies with your other team members to cover any weaknesses!",
